import os
import cv2
import mediapipe as mp
import json
import numpy as np
import joblib
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Paths
image_folder = r'C:\Users\Istiaque Ahmed\Documents\AIDojo\Keypoint-Based\Final Test\InputImage_and_json'
output_folder = r'C:\Users\Istiaque Ahmed\Documents\AIDojo\Keypoint-Based\Final Test\OutputImage_and_json'

# Model and Label Encoder paths
model_path = r'C:\Users\Istiaque Ahmed\Documents\AIDojo\Keypoint-Based\Final Test\ModelPreparation\svm_action_classifier.pkl'
label_encoder_path = r'C:\Users\Istiaque Ahmed\Documents\AIDojo\Keypoint-Based\Final Test\ModelPreparation\label_encoder.pkl'

# Load the trained model and label encoder
svm_model = joblib.load(model_path)
label_encoder = joblib.load(label_encoder_path)

# Mediapipe Pose setup
mp_pose = mp.solutions.pose
pose = mp_pose.Pose(static_image_mode=True, min_detection_confidence=0.5)

# Enhanced skeleton connections
connections = [
    (0, 1), (1, 2), (2, 3), (3, 7),  # Head to upper body
    (0, 4), (4, 5), (5, 6),          # Head to shoulders
    (5, 6), (5, 7), (7, 9),          # Left shoulder to elbow to wrist
    (6, 8), (8, 10),                 # Right shoulder to elbow to wrist
    (5, 11), (6, 12),                # Left hip to shoulder, right hip to shoulder
    (11, 12), (11, 13), (13, 15),    # Left hip to knee to ankle
    (12, 14), (14, 16),              # Right hip to knee to ankle
    (11, 23), (12, 24),              # Hips to left and right legs
    (23, 25), (25, 27), (27, 29),    # Left leg detailed connections
    (24, 26), (26, 28), (28, 30),    # Right leg detailed connections
    (15, 19), (15, 21),              # Left foot details
    (16, 20), (16, 22)               # Right foot details
]

# Ensure output directory exists
os.makedirs(output_folder, exist_ok=True)

# Number of keypoints expected by the model
expected_features = 99  # Adjust according to the model's training setup (33 landmarks × 3 attributes)

# Process each image in the folder
for image_filename in os.listdir(image_folder):
    if image_filename.lower().endswith(('.jpeg', '.jpg', '.png')):
        image_path = os.path.join(image_folder, image_filename)
        image = cv2.imread(image_path)
        if image is None:
            print(f"Error reading image: {image_path}")
            continue
        height, width, _ = image.shape

        # Generate a unique image ID
        image_id = os.path.splitext(image_filename)[0]

        # Convert BGR image to RGB and process
        rgb_image = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
        results = pose.process(rgb_image)

        # Check for landmarks
        if results.pose_landmarks:
            keypoints = []
            x_points, y_points, visibility = [], [], []
            # Extract all 33 landmarks
            for lm in results.pose_landmarks.landmark:
                x, y, v = lm.x * width, lm.y * height, lm.visibility
                keypoints.extend([x, y, v])
                x_points.append(x)
                y_points.append(y)
                visibility.append(v)

            # Validate the number of features
            if len(keypoints) != expected_features:
                print(f"Skipping {image_filename}: Extracted {len(keypoints)} features, expected {expected_features}")
                continue

            # Classify keypoints using the trained model
            try:
                keypoints_np = np.array(keypoints).reshape(1, -1)
                predicted_label = svm_model.predict(keypoints_np)[0]
                predicted_class = label_encoder.inverse_transform([predicted_label])[0]
            except Exception as e:
                print(f"Error classifying keypoints for {image_filename}: {e}")
                continue

            # Create keypoints-only image
            keypoint_image = image.copy()
            for x, y, v in zip(x_points, y_points, visibility):
                if v > 0:  # If visibility is greater than 0
                    cv2.circle(keypoint_image, (int(x), int(y)), radius=5, color=(255, 0, 0), thickness=-1)  # Red circles

            # Save keypoints-only image
            keypoint_image_path = os.path.join(output_folder, f"{image_id}_keypoints.jpg")
            cv2.imwrite(keypoint_image_path, cv2.cvtColor(keypoint_image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))

            # Display the keypoints-only image
            plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
            plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(keypoint_image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
            plt.axis('off')
            plt.title(f"Keypoints Image (ID: {image_id}, Class: {predicted_class})")
            plt.show()

            # Create skeleton connection image
            skeleton_image = keypoint_image.copy()
            for start, end in connections:
                if visibility[start] > 0 and visibility[end] > 0:  # Only draw if both keypoints are visible
                    start_point = (int(x_points[start]), int(y_points[start]))
                    end_point = (int(x_points[end]), int(y_points[end]))
                    cv2.line(skeleton_image, start_point, end_point, color=(0, 255, 0), thickness=2)  # Green lines

            # Save skeleton image
            skeleton_image_path = os.path.join(output_folder, f"{image_id}_skeleton.jpg")
            cv2.imwrite(skeleton_image_path, cv2.cvtColor(skeleton_image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))

            # Display the skeleton connection image
            plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
            plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(skeleton_image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
            plt.axis('off')
            plt.title(f"Skeleton Image (ID: {image_id}, Class: {predicted_class})")
            plt.show()

            # Create JSON data for this image
            json_data = {
                "image_id": image_id,
                "keypoints": keypoints,
                "predicted_class": predicted_class
            }

            # Save the JSON file with the image ID as the filename
            json_output_path = os.path.join(output_folder, f"{image_id}.json")
            with open(json_output_path, 'w') as f:
                json.dump(json_data, f, indent=4)

            # Print save status
            print(f"Image ID: {image_id}, Predicted Class: {predicted_class}")
            print(f"Saved Keypoints Image: {keypoint_image_path}")
            print(f"Saved Skeleton Image: {skeleton_image_path}")

print(f"All classified data saved to {output_folder}")
pose.close()
